DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE
CRIMINAL INVESTIGATIONS DIVISION

EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT

---

This Employment Contract ("Contract")
is entered into as of March 3, 2025,

between the Department of Justice,
Criminal Investigations Division
("the Division")

and the undersigned employee ("Employee").

---

1. POSITION

The Employee is engaged in the role of
Forensic Intelligence Analyst.

The Employee will report to
Det. Rodriguez

and operate within the
Criminal Investigations Division.

---

2. START DATE

Employment shall commence on
Monday, April 14, 2025.

---

3. COMPENSATION

The Employee shall receive a
monthly salary of $5,400,

payable on the last business day
of each month.

---

4. WORKING HOURS

Standard working hours are
40 hours per week,
Monday through Friday.

Overtime may be required
at the Division's discretion

and will be compensated
in accordance with applicable law.

---

5. PROBATIONARY PERIOD

The Employee will serve a
probationary period of 90 days

from the commencement of employment.

During this period,
employment may be terminated
by either party

with 5 days written notice.

---

6. VACATION

The Employee is entitled to
15 paid vacation days
per calendar year,

prorated during the first year
of employment.

---

7. NON-COMPETE

Upon termination of employment,

the Employee agrees not to engage in,
consult for, or be employed by any
organization conducting investigations

in direct conflict with the Division's
active caseload

for a period of 12 months.

---

8. GOVERNING LAW

This Contract shall be governed by
and construed in accordance with

the laws of the District of Columbia.

---

9. ENTIRE AGREEMENT

This Contract, together with:

- Non-Disclosure Agreement
- Employee Handbook

constitutes the entire agreement
between the parties.

